default&#xa0;default&#xa0;defaultShort Biographydefault&#xa0;
defaultDr. Judith Curry is Professor and Chair of the School of Earth and Atmospheric Sciences at the Georgia Institute of Technology and President of Climate Forecast Applications Ne
defaulttwork (CFAN). Dr. Curry received a Ph.D. in atmospheric science from the University of Chicago in
default 1982. 
defaultPrior to joining the faculty at Georgia Tech, she held faculty positions at the University of Colorado, Penn State University and Purdue University. Dr.
default Curry’s research interests span a variety of topics in climate; current interests include 
defaultclimate dynamics of the polar regions
default, climate feedback processes associated with clouds and sea ice, and the climate dynamics of hurricanes. 
defaultShe has published over 190 journal articles and is author of the books 
defaultThermodynamics of Atmospheres and Oceans 
defaultand
default Thermodynamics
default, 
defaultKinetics and Microphysics of Clouds.
default  She is also Editor of the 
defaultEncyclopedia of Atmospheric Sciences
default. 
defaultShe is a prominent pub
defaultlic spokesperson on issues associated with the integrity of climate 
defaultresearch
default, and 
defaultis proprietor of
default the weblog Climate Etc.
default judithcurry.com. 
defaultDr. Curry currently serves on the NASA Advisory Council 
defaultEarth Science Subcommittee and the DOE Biological and Enviro
defaultnmental Research Advisory Committee, and 
defaulthas recently served on the National Academies Climate Research Committee and the Space Studies Board and the NOAA Climate Working Group. Dr. Curry is a Fellow of the American Meteorological Society, the American Ass
defaultociation for the Advancement of Science, and the American Geophysical Union. 
